    "This advantage can be attributed to the straightforward and parallelizable structure of our suggested model.",
    "RNN models, on the other hand, encounter difficulties because of their sequential nature, leading to longer training durations, especially when working with datasets containing prolonged sequences.",
    "The suggested model's interpretability when compared to RNN is also a key advantage.",
    "While RNN models are difficult to interpret, our proposed model provides more clarity and is simpler to understand.",
    "In healthcare applications, this interpretability can be quite helpful because it gives medical practitioners insights into the underlying causes of heart failure (HF) prediction and speeds up the decision-making process."
